{
  "stem": "1917.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "It was more difficult to stay in a place that I was hoping to see in the conditions that it was.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And so my aunt anyway wanted us to move to the city to Kolozsvar-- Cluj.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And the cousin took us by train to my aunt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I didn't even stay longer than one day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I could not cope with the desolate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The place was so haunted, so empty, that there was no-- no reason for us to stay there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- so no, I could not.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I do not know if they were anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I do know that years later, when I went back the following summer for summer vacation, and-- and I went to see the neighbors.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was in a little bit better shape and talking, they said, well, we couldn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- I saw my mother's towels, tablecloths, because mother had everything monogrammed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I would look at it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I would recognize it and say, oh, yeah, I just took that to save it for you when you got back.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think they were very glad that we were taken away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think that they did not want us to return.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It got very bad toward 1948 and '49 and '50.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That when we finally got our visa to immigrate to Israel, I did want to go back and maybe just see the house, maybe find my grandfather's grave.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we knew that there were all kind of stories of people that are attacking former landowners, and that it was not wise for us to go back to the village, because we might be attacked.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The only reason that Miriam and I were not put on trial, because we were war orphans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were not jailed.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
